<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I did this defense raising strategy last nite.....allowing mobs to pound me to get my points up.  I discovered that this only works with blues and that it is, as you might expect, boring.  I spent a half an hour doing this and raised my defense two points.  I also discovered something else which I suspected for awhile.....that our piercing is pretty useless as an offensive weapon.  My skill is 'master'.....130 something but it doesn't damage past the high twenties.  Without casting anything but heals on myself and flash of light on mob, I found my piercing will not do enough damage to move the mobs health bar.....its own natural regeneration heals the damage.  Perhaps its the blues I was fighting....in Overthere the blues have many more hp than in Lake of Ill Omen.
</FONT>
