<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Slam, shamans can hit well into their 40's with spears later, so it gets better.  I find though that if you're off even, say, two or three points from having offense maxed from your level, you hit a LOT less.  Every point of offense skill really seems to count a lot.<P>Also, guys, if you get in a jam of having too little natural defense/AC that it took you a few levels or a lot of levels to get into, be realistic and don't expect to get out of it quickly.  It takes even longer to get out of trouble than in it, because the skill raises can come VERY slowly.  You don't even always get five per level.  So you can be trying your hardest and still getting further behind every level.  But thanks to the wonder of hell levels and perseverance, you can eventually max all your melee skills and defense/AC and offense.  You will be a MUCH tougher and better shaman when you do, so give it a shot.<P>Remember, anyone can just put on wisdom gear; you can't "put on" melee stats.  You must earn them.  If you go the lazy way, you'll get results that reflect it.<P>If you'd like to be able to melee at 51 like I and other shamans even higher than I do, ya gotta earn it.  May be boring, but that's the breaks.  <P>If you slack off, though, you have no one but yourself to blame.<P>Well, except perhaps the other shamans who told you melee couldn't be done.
</FONT>
