<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I am only a level 20 Shaman, thus, what I  may say may not be applicable to the higher levels.<P>I have maxed out my offense and defense. The key is that shamans should solo enough to keep the these skills maxed at each level. To avoid boredom, I cast dots and root on mobs plus debuff their strength and AC. I then malee till they are dead. Atleast I am getting experience. One little trick that I use when my hp starts getting low is to cast Flash of light and back off. The mob runs for a few seconds. I then heal my self twice (if lucky). This allows for more malee.<P>For some reason, I am finding weapon skills seem to take longer. Maybe its just bad luck. Again, you need to solo or participate in the malee with groups.<P>Hope this helps
