<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Why do people suggest using the slow line when trying to increase defense? When you slow a mob you are slowing the rate you get hit which slows the rate your defense increases.<P>This is what I do for soloing. (as a lvl 26 shammy who is working on skills)<P>Buff with regen, sow, ac, str, stam, agil, and dex.<P>Pull with malise<P>Run to spot you have specced to fight at.<P>When mob gets into range land EB on it.<P>Turn on melee.<P>Cast disempower on it.<P>Renew EB when needed.<P>When mob starts running root it so you get hit more.<P>If you need to heal root it (since you cast malise root will last much better), step back and heal.<P>If you need to run root it and run.<P><BR>I have been doing this in loio against sabertooth grimalkins, goblin warriors, and goblin warlords.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
